<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-10-28T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-10-28T23:00:00-05:00" n="804" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d804">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">894.00/820: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-10-29T13:00:00+09:00">October 29, 1938—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 29—12:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>691. The following appointments to the Cabinet have just been announced:
                            Hachiro Arita, Minister for Foreign Affairs; Yoshiaki Hatta, Minister
                            for Overseas Affairs. Arita was formerly Minister for Foreign Affairs
                            and Hatta was formerly Vice President of the South Manchuria Railway
                            Company.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>